         <OBJECT_CONTRACT>
            <TITLE>
               <P>Bus Tender Route Package Bergen South and Route Package West</P>
            </TITLE>
            <REFERENCE_NUMBER>HFK-17-0174</REFERENCE_NUMBER>
            <CPV_MAIN>
               <CPV_CODE CODE="60100000"/>
            </CPV_MAIN>
            <TYPE_CONTRACT CTYPE="SERVICES"/>
            <SHORT_DESCR>
               <P>The aim of the procurement is to get an operator(s) for the 2 route packages 'Bergen south' and 'west'. The routes in the area are mainly built on the current lines and route offer, the ambition is a continuous line network and an offer that allows as many people as possible to get to important destinations.</P>
               <P>The current contracts (per 2017) (maximum take up):</P>
               <P>Bergen south: 6 252 575 route kilometers 123 buses.</P>
               <P>West: 5 109 829 route kilometers 133 buses.</P>
               <P>Both Bergen south and west and areas where Skyss expect the need for public transport to grow until 2030.</P>
               <P>Both route package west and route package Bergen south are to be carried out with 100 % renewable energy. Skyss shall have the right to ask the operator to change the propulsion technology during the contract period.</P>
               <P>Route package west includes an option for the Contracting Authority to require that parts of the route production are carried out with biogas.</P>
            </SHORT_DESCR>
